                    textOnly="&lt;p>&lt;span class=&quot;body-copy-large&quot;>PALO ALTO, CA--(Marketwired - Jun 26, 2014) - HP (NYSE: HPQ) today announced that Mondelz International has signed a five-year, multimillion dollar agreement with HP to transform its support environment for SAP solutions, driving business-process improvement for the global snacking powerhouse that spans leading brands such as Cadbury, Nabisco and Oreo.&lt;/span>&lt;/p>&#xa;&lt;p>&lt;span class=&quot;body-copy-large&quot;>Under the agreement terms, HP will complement the infrastructure services it already provides Mondelz International with&lt;a rel=&quot;nofollow&quot; href=&quot;http://www8.hp.com/us/en/business-services/it-services.html?compURI=1079016&quot;>applications services for SAP solutions&lt;/a> to transform the computing environment to be more business-outcome focused. Mondelz International will also use HP-implemented &amp;quot;Run SAP Like a Factory&amp;quot; tools and processes to effectively monitor operations. The transformation of the SAP solution-based environment will enable better decisions and business outcomes, including increased productivity.&lt;/span>&lt;/p>&#xa;&lt;p>&lt;span class=&quot;body-copy-large&quot;>&amp;quot;This agreement represents a strategic step to leverage our investment in SAP solutions, improve operations quality and lower costs,&amp;quot; said Mark Dajani, chief information officer and EBS officer, Mondelz International. &amp;quot;As a trusted partner, HP has a clear vision of the Industrialized Delivery Model for SAP solutions that reflects industry and technology expertise, combined with experience in managing complex environments that will boost the business value of our investment.&amp;quot;&lt;/span>&lt;/p>&#xa;&lt;p>&lt;span class=&quot;body-copy-large&quot;>HP will use its Industrialized Delivery Model for delivery of SAP applications to consistently manage Mondelz International's infrastructure as well as its applications development and maintenance functions. This, coupled with teams focused on improving and industrializing the efficiencies in their SAP solution landscape, will allow Mondelz International the opportunity to take advantage of globally consistent delivery.&lt;/span>&lt;/p>&#xa;&lt;p>&lt;span class=&quot;body-copy-large&quot;>&lt;i>&amp;quot;The recent transition to HP was seamless, and I am thrilled with the speed and quality of the execution,&amp;quot; said Matthias Herzog, senior director, Enterprise Services, Mondelz International. &amp;quot;We could not have dreamt of a better way to start our transformation journey of SAP solutions.&amp;quot;&lt;/i>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>&#xa;&lt;p>&lt;span class=&quot;body-copy-large&quot;>HP has provided strategic infrastructure hosting services for SAP solutions at Mondelz International since 2006 and will continue to provide these services from HP data centers in Germany, the United States and from application delivery centers across the globe.&lt;/span>&lt;/p>&#xa;&lt;p>&lt;span class=&quot;body-copy-large&quot;>&lt;i>&amp;quot;As a trusted partner to Mondelz International, we will help transform the company's business to enable growth and meet increasing customer demand for its products across the globe,&amp;quot;&lt;/i> &lt;i>said &lt;/i>&lt;a rel=&quot;nofollow&quot; href=&quot;http://www8.hp.com/us/en/hp-information/executive-team/team.html#mike-nefkens&quot;>&lt;i>Mike Nefkens&lt;/i>&lt;/a>&lt;i>, executive vice president and general manager, HP Enterprise Services. &amp;quot;In addition to helping ensure the infrastructure for running SAP applications is reliable, the HP team will combine our technical knowledge with our business and industry expertise to create a platform focused on achieving better business outcomes for Mondelz International operations worldwide.&amp;quot;&lt;/i>&lt;/span>&lt;/p>&#xa;&lt;p>&lt;span class=&quot;body-copy-large&quot;>&lt;b>About HP&lt;br>&#xa; &lt;/b>HP creates new possibilities for technology to have a meaningful impact on people, businesses, governments and society. With the broadest technology portfolio spanning printing, personal systems, software, services and IT infrastructure, HP delivers solutions for customers' most complex challenges in every region of the world. More information about HP is available at &lt;a rel=&quot;nofollow&quot; href=&quot;http://www.hp.com/&quot;>http://www.hp.com&lt;/a>.&lt;/span>&lt;/p>&#xa;&lt;p>&lt;span class=&quot;body-copy-large&quot;>SAP and all SAP logos are trademarks or registered trademarks of SAP AG in Germany and in several other countries.&lt;/span>&lt;/p>&#xa;&lt;p>&lt;span class=&quot;body-copy-large&quot;>2014 Hewlett-Packard Development Company, L.P. The information contained herein is subject to change without notice. The only warranties for HP products and services are set forth in the express warranty statements accompanying such products and services. Nothing herein should be construed as constituting an additional warranty. HP shall not be liable for technical or editorial errors or omissions contained herein.&lt;/span>&lt;/p>&#xa;"/>
